{
  "texts": [
    "The model considers the temporal data gathered from the instances.",
    "The authors (Liu et al., 2020) have described a technique that combines an LSTM network with a multi-time sparse smooth network to identify early and late MCIs using multi-time points of resting-state fMRI.",
    "Specifically, resting-state fMRI data obtained across various time points is used to construct a sparse, smooth brain network.",
    "Features are then extracted and longitudinally analyzed using an attention-based stacking bidirectional LSTM.",
    "The authors (Rajasree and Brintha Rajakumari, 2024) developed a four-phase method for early diagnosis of Alzheimer's disease: pre-processing, feature extraction, feature selection, and classification."
  ]
}